  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-01 test)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed at the COU level; all 13 credibility factors are assessed. Decision: Accepted. This synthetic package is constructed to trigger COMPOUND-01: the bound claim carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom provenance (W-EP-01, Critical) and the primary validation result carries no hasUncertaintyQuantification field (W-AL-01, High), both conditions holding simultaneously on the same UnitOfAssurance.",
